S

SecureString - Class in bjad.common.string
Wrapper for keeping strings secured by encrypting them in memory, or to decrypt/encrypt strings from setting files or other external sources.
SecureString() - Constructor for class bjad.common.string.SecureString
Creates an empty secure string with a randomized key and salt value.
SecureString(String) - Constructor for class bjad.common.string.SecureString
Creates a securestring for the value passed using a randomized key and salt value.
SecureString(String, String) - Constructor for class bjad.common.string.SecureString
Creates an empty Secure String but sets the encryption key and the salting value for future operations.
SecureString(String, String, String) - Constructor for class bjad.common.string.SecureString
Creates the secure string with the key, salt, and initial value set within it.
SecureStringException - Exception in bjad.common.string
Exception for the secure string class that will capture any of the encryption exceptions and encapsulate them in a RuntimeException so that you don't need to catch them for things like bad Algorithm exceptions unless you need to.
SecureStringException(Exception) - Constructor for exception bjad.common.string.SecureStringException
Constructor, setting the original exception for the secure string exception that will be optional to catch.
setFromBase64String(String) - Method in class bjad.common.string.SecureString
Sets the encrypted value within the object from the base 64 value passed to the function.
setString(String) - Method in class bjad.common.string.SecureString
Sets the string value that is to be stored securely in the object.
